<p><b>Temporary tax??? That’s funny as well as an oxymoron.</b></p>
<p>The &#8220;tolls&#8221; (AKA taxes) on the Bay Bridge and Golden Gate Bridge, were both &#8220;temporary&#8221;, until the bonds that built them were paid off, they started collecting the tolls when the two opened, November 1936 for the Bay Bridge and May 3197 for the Golden Gate, construction bonds were paid off n 10 years. Guess what, BOTH still have the &#8220;temporary&#8221; tolls, 80 years later! No such thing as a &#8220;temporary&#8221; tax.</p>
